------------------------------------------------------------------------- 2Ô∏è‚É£ What is Inheritance ? ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
it is one of the priciple of oops, where a subclass inherits properties and methods from a superclass (not properties value only variable eg - if parent age me koi value rkhoge jaise ki
parent ka object create kiya or usme p.age=17; to vo child ke object me nhi jayega only wo variable ke name le skta hai ), promoting code reusability and creating an IS-A relationship.
Child = Subclass / Derived class
Parent = Superclass / Base class
note:- jab child bol rhe ho to parent bolo  and jab derived class bol rhe ho to base class bolo or jab subclass bol rhe ho to super class bolo.
Example:
Dog is-a Animal üê∂ ‚Üí inherits legs, eat(), sleep() from Animal.

üî∑ Why?
‚úî Code reusability
‚úî Avoid duplication
‚úî Easy maintenance
‚úî Supports polymorphism
‚úî Extends functionality of existing class

üî∑ Types of Inheritance :
| Type         | Description                            | Supported in Java?                                              | Example                                              |
| ------------ | -------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| Single       | 1 parent ‚Üí 1 child                     | ‚úî Supported                                                     | Animal ‚Üí Dog                                         |
| Multilevel   | Parent ‚Üí Child ‚Üí Grandchild            | ‚úî Supported                                                     | Animal ‚Üí Dog ‚Üí Puppy                                 |
| Hierarchical | One parent, many children              | ‚úî Supported                                                     | Animal ‚Üí Dog, Cat                                    |
| Multiple     | 1 child inherits from multiple parents | ‚ùå **Class level not allowed**‚úî Allowed using **interfaces**    |class C extends A,B ‚ùå<br>class C implements I1, I2 ‚úî|
| Hybrid       | Combination of two or more types of inheritance  | single + multilevel + hierarchical  (generally interfaces ke throurh hota h   | (Mix of above)                |

Note:- In Java, variables (instance & static) are not overridden, they are only hidden; therefore variable access depends on the reference type, not on the object.
       Because variables use compile-time binding, not runtime polymorphism.
      - Static method ke case me bhi exact same rule lagta hai jo variables par lagta hai. Static methods are NOT overridden, they are HIDDEN; method call dependson the reference type,
        not on the object.
ex - 
FOR VARIABLES (STATIC & NON-STATIC) :
class A { int x = 10;}
class B extends A { int x = 20;}
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        A obj = new B(); System.out.println(obj.x);} // output: 10

FOR Method Example :
class A {
    void show() {
        System.out.println("A");}}

class B extends A {
    void show() {
        System.out.println("B"); }}
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        A obj = new B();
        obj.show(); }} // Output: B

 



WHAT IS DIAMOND PROBLEM ?
jab ek child multiple parents ko inherit krega(technically java me possible nhi h) or dono parent me ek common method hoga to child class ke liye diamond problem create krega 
isko avoid krne ke liye interface ka use hota hai
Note:- by default jab v ek class bnti hai java me to wo single inheritance hoti hai because by default object class ko inherit krti hai .


This keyword :
it refers instance of current class.
- properties access kr skte ho
- method access kr skte ho
- even static chije v access kr skte ho
- it can't be use inside static area like method,block.
- can call current class constructor like, this(), this(age) etc. but during constructor call it should be the first stament except for method call kbhi v use kr skte ho.
- using this keyword Constructor chaining must be linear, not circular. it can be same class (without inheritance) and with inheritance v hota hai.

Super keyword :
it refers to immediate parent class.
- super.method() aur super.variable Child class ke kisi bhi instance method se call ho sakta hai / Child class ke constructor se bhi call ho sakta hai.
- method ya variable call krte time First statement hona zaroori nahi. agr constructor se kr rhe hai to orna nhi
- Static context (static method / main) se nahi
- can call immediate parent class constructor like, super(), super(age) etc. Parent class constructor ko super() sirf aur sirf child class ke constructor se hi call kiya ja sakta hai.
  and First statement hona mandatory.

Final keyword :
final makes something unchangeable:
- value change is not allowed.
- method override is not allowed.
- class inheritance is not allowed.


üî∑ Constructor Rules :
- jab v hum ek class bnate hai or koi constructor assign nhi krte hai to automatically usko ek constructor mil jata hai jo default constructor hota h.
- jab class B extend krti hai A ko to jab v A ka obj bnayenge to A as usual constructor call hoga but jab v Child ka obj bnate ho to child ka constructor as well as uske parent ka constructor
  call hota hai top to down order me mtlb parent ka constructor phle call hoga then child ka constructor call hoga.

ANALYSIS CASE-1:
A()
‚¨Ü
B()
A a = new A(); // A class constructor called.
B b = new B(); // A class constructor called,then B class constructor called.

